odio-api (0.16.1) trixie; urgency=low

  Tracklist & Client Naming Fixes

  * MPRIS: duplicate TrackAdded signals no longer duplicate the cached
    tracklist entry (track IDs are unique per spec).
  * PulseAudio: clients registering empty names (e.g. spotifyd) get a
    derived name — application.name, then the process binary — fixing
    the empty label and broken mute/volume routes (#130).

 -- Mathieu Réquillart <mathieu.requillart@gmail.com>  Thu, 23 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000


odio-api (0.16.0) trixie; urgency=low

  MPRIS Tracklist

  * MPRIS TrackList interface support: tracklist loaded into the player
    cache, kept live via D-Bus signals, with dedicated SSE events.
  * New endpoints: get the tracklist, jump to a track, add and remove
    tracks (capability-gated, tracks referenced by ID).
  * UI: a toggle on the player card switches the cover to the tracklist
    (current track highlighted, tap to jump, per-track remove), with
    view and scroll position preserved across live refreshes.
  * UI: tap the cover to zoom it fullscreen.

 -- Mathieu Réquillart <mathieu.requillart@gmail.com>  Thu, 23 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000


odio-api (0.15.1) trixie; urgency=low

  Self-Upgrade Backend

  * New upgrade backend: pluggable detector/executor scripts with a
    persisted run lifecycle (idle/running/failed) surviving restarts.
  * GET /upgrade status and POST trigger endpoints, with SSE progress
    events; internal units hidden from the public services list.
  * UI: upgrade badge in the header with progress ring and failure state.
  * Systemd backend: internal user units and fire-and-forget triggers.

