odio-api (0.3.0) trixie; urgency=low

  Complete implementation of MPRIS backend with auto-discovery, real-time event
  listening, and full playback control for D-Bus media players.

  * Add MPRIS D-Bus backend for media player control
  * Add auto-discovery of MPRIS-compatible players (Spotify, VLC, Firefox, etc.)
  * Add event-driven updates via D-Bus signals (PropertiesChanged, NameOwnerChanged)
  * Add full playback control: Play, Pause, Stop, Next, Previous, Seek, SetPosition
  * Add volume and playback mode management (Loop, Shuffle)
  * Add metadata retrieval with proper type handling
  * Add multi-player concurrent control support
  * Add capability-based validation (CanPlay, CanPause, CanSeek, etc.)
  * Add REST API endpoints for all MPRIS operations
  * Add configuration options: mpris.enabled and mpris.timeout (default: 5s)
  * Optimize D-Bus calls with batched GetAll operations (~85% reduction)
  * Implement intelligent position heartbeat with lazy start/stop
  * Add comprehensive timeout handling to all D-Bus operations
  * Add unique name caching to eliminate repeated lookups
  * Add semantic error types: PlayerNotFoundError, CapabilityError, ValidationError
  * Add bus name validation against injection attacks
  * Add prefixed logging ([mpris]) for observability
  * Add padding on WARN and INFO logs for readability

 -- Mathieu Réquillart <mathieu.requillart@gmail.com>  Thu, 05 Feb 2026 16:00:00 +0000


